        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
            <p>The Harry and Mae Millstone Papers contain records of Mae Kaplan Millstone (1913-2009) and Harry Millstone (1907-1999), labor activists and organizers. Mae Kaplan Millstone and Harry Millstone met in Detroit while organizing with the C.I.O. and later married in 1938. The collection includes documentation of their work as organizers and activists in the 1970s and 1980s. Also included is a variety of subject files regarding women's history, and women in the workplace. Mae Millstone was the editor of the women's pages of the   newspaper of York, Pennsylvania in the 1960s. Included in the collection are women's pages from the   dating from 1962-1965, 1967, 1970 and 1971.</p>
        </scopecontent>
